48
00:05:02,304 --> 00:05:03,604
Hi, mom.

49
00:05:04,273 --> 00:05:08,143
Faye, how about letting your
old ma sit in her chair?

50
00:05:08,144 --> 00:05:10,145
I don't feel so good, mama.

51
00:05:10,146 --> 00:05:11,913
No? How was the movie?

52
00:05:12,082 --> 00:05:13,649
Well, it was scary.

53
00:05:13,683 --> 00:05:15,585
Flying saucers and monsters.

54
00:05:15,586 --> 00:05:16,886
Annie cried.

55
00:05:17,321 --> 00:05:18,955
- Did not!
- Did too!

56
00:05:18,956 --> 00:05:19,956
Did not!

57
00:05:20,690 --> 00:05:21,157
Did too!

58
00:05:21,358 --> 00:05:21,857
Did not!

59
00:05:22,058 --> 00:05:22,625
Did too!

60
00:05:23,026 --> 00:05:24,026
- Did not!
- Did too!

61
00:05:24,027 --> 00:05:24,527
Did not!

62
00:05:24,761 --> 00:05:25,930
You two, pipe down.

63
00:05:25,931 --> 00:05:27,131
Did not, did not!

64
00:05:27,132 --> 00:05:28,132
Did too.

65
00:05:28,333 --> 00:05:29,633
Look, mama.

66
00:05:30,368 --> 00:05:31,668
Oh, isn't that pretty?

67
00:05:31,669 --> 00:05:33,036
Isn't that mine?

68
00:05:33,305 --> 00:05:34,605
I don't know.

69
00:05:35,674 --> 00:05:38,441
Where'd you guys
get all this candy?

70
00:05:38,877 --> 00:05:40,979
I just gave you enough
money to go to the movies.

71
00:05:40,980 --> 00:05:43,013
You took your own popcorn.

72
00:05:43,617 --> 00:05:44,917
Lynn?

73
00:05:45,385 --> 00:05:46,685
I don't know.

74
00:05:47,321 --> 00:05:48,621
Faye?

75
00:05:48,822 --> 00:05:50,122
It wasn't me.

76
00:05:50,790 --> 00:05:52,090
Murray.

77
00:06:00,268 --> 00:06:01,835
Pipe down, you two.

78
00:06:02,204 --> 00:06:04,237
You're giving me an ulcer.

79
00:06:06,174 --> 00:06:08,209
Mrs. Lacey?
Your husband home?

80
00:06:08,210 --> 00:06:10,545
No he's not.
What's the beef this time?

81
00:06:10,546 --> 00:06:12,347
- Mama, I was just...
- You shut up.

82
00:06:12,348 --> 00:06:14,383
We had a complain from
the phone company.

83
00:06:14,384 --> 00:06:16,918
Your kid had a string of
their coin returns plugged.

84
00:06:16,919 --> 00:06:20,456
That's what you collared him for?
Penny ante crap?

85
00:06:20,457 --> 00:06:23,176
There's real crime,
and you're busting kids

86
00:06:23,177 --> 00:06:25,445
for boosting nickels from the
goddamn phone company?

87
00:06:25,446 --> 00:06:27,281
- Tell 'em, ma.
- You, pipe down.

88
00:06:27,482 --> 00:06:28,949
I've had a rotten day,

89
00:06:29,073 --> 00:06:30,251
a really rotten day,

90
00:06:30,252 --> 00:06:32,692
and wouldn't be in the mood for this,
if it came with flowers.

91
00:06:32,716 --> 00:06:34,555
You keeping him
or throwing him back?

92
00:06:34,556 --> 00:06:36,291
He ain't worth the paperwork.

93
00:06:36,292 --> 00:06:38,059
Just take this as a warning

94
00:06:38,060 --> 00:06:39,895
and keep your Dillinger
off the street.

95
00:06:39,896 --> 00:06:41,763
Watch the name calling
and get out.

96
00:06:41,764 --> 00:06:43,531
I take care of my own.

97
00:06:44,700 --> 00:06:46,568
Do that, lady, 'cause next time

98
00:06:46,569 --> 00:06:49,336
we might not be
in such a good mood.

99
00:06:50,174 --> 00:06:53,276
So the shoeshine business
has been good lately, huh?

100
00:06:53,277 --> 00:06:54,917
Been doing real good
on tips, you told me.

101
00:06:54,941 --> 00:06:56,212
Well, I did get...

102
00:06:56,213 --> 00:06:57,713
who did you lie to?

103
00:06:57,714 --> 00:06:59,014
Your mother.

104
00:07:02,687 --> 00:07:04,720
Go get your father's belt.

105
00:07:11,697 --> 00:07:12,997
That night,

106
00:07:12,999 --> 00:07:15,032
my mother made a decision.

107
00:07:15,802 --> 00:07:17,837
She didn't bother asking us
what we wanted to do.

108
00:07:17,838 --> 00:07:19,138
She never did.

109
00:07:20,140 --> 00:07:21,874
And once mama made up her mind,

110
00:07:21,875 --> 00:07:23,908
there was no stopping her.

111
00:07:29,467 --> 00:07:30,767
I'm thirsty.

112
00:07:35,006 --> 00:07:37,642
Tomorrow morning we're moving
out of this toilet of a city.

113
00:07:37,643 --> 00:07:38,943
Huh?

114
00:07:39,245 --> 00:07:40,545
Don't "huh" me.

115
00:07:42,414 --> 00:07:44,548
We're going to find
a decent town to live in

116
00:07:44,549 --> 00:07:47,119
and a proper home,
a house of our own.

117
00:07:47,120 --> 00:07:48,420
That's that.

118
00:07:50,791 --> 00:07:53,292
I ain't leaving. I ain't
leaving the neighborhood.

119
00:07:53,293 --> 00:07:55,128
One more "ain't,"
I soap out that mouth.

120
00:07:55,129 --> 00:07:57,496
You're going.
We're all going.

121
00:07:59,533 --> 00:08:01,566
I ain't...
I'm not going.

122
00:08:03,137 --> 00:08:05,037
We're leaving this city.

123
00:08:05,340 --> 00:08:07,875
I don't have the chance
of an ice cube in a frying pan

124
00:08:07,876 --> 00:08:11,109
of making things better
as long as we stay.

125
00:08:12,715 --> 00:08:14,216
I'm sick of moving around.

126
00:08:14,217 --> 00:08:15,517
That's too bad.

127
00:08:16,019 --> 00:08:17,920
You're the man of the house.

128
00:08:17,921 --> 00:08:20,455
Have you forgotten
the promise you made me?

129
00:08:20,456 --> 00:08:22,826
You swore you'd help me with
your brothers and sisters,

130
00:08:22,827 --> 00:08:25,394
that I could
always count on you.

131
00:08:25,395 --> 00:08:27,162
You gave me your word.

132
00:08:30,801 --> 00:08:32,101
Yeah.

133
00:08:32,904 --> 00:08:34,804
I know it won't be easy,

134
00:08:34,889 --> 00:08:37,789
but I can't do it
without you, Shayne.

135
00:08:38,492 --> 00:08:40,059
Now get some sleep.

136
00:08:49,238 --> 00:08:51,138
I'll make you a promise.

137
00:08:52,408 --> 00:08:53,809
You do this for me,

138
00:08:53,810 --> 00:08:55,910
and we'll never move again.

139
00:08:56,396 --> 00:08:57,696
Promise.

140
00:09:06,324 --> 00:09:07,624
So we left L.A.

141
00:09:07,858 --> 00:09:09,760
We sold everything we could.

142
00:09:09,761 --> 00:09:11,721
What we couldn't sell or
fit into our '48 Plymouth

143
00:09:11,745 --> 00:09:13,045
we gave away.

144
00:09:13,699 --> 00:09:16,139
When most families take a trip,
they know where they're going.

145
00:09:16,163 --> 00:09:17,163
Not us.

146
00:09:17,202 --> 00:09:19,137
Mama just pointed the car,

147
00:09:19,138 --> 00:09:20,539
sort of north and sort of east,

148
00:09:20,540 --> 00:09:21,973
and away we went.

149
00:09:22,442 --> 00:09:25,243
Ma, would you tell Murray
and Annie to quit it?

150
00:09:25,244 --> 00:09:26,811
Would you two stop?

151
00:09:27,147 --> 00:09:28,514
- Haaa!
- Mama!

152
00:09:29,133 --> 00:09:30,900
Nobody gets the bunny.

153
00:09:35,489 --> 00:09:36,922
I did not, Craig!

154
00:09:37,192 --> 00:09:37,925
Yes, you did!

155
00:09:37,926 --> 00:09:38,993
Did not!

156
00:09:38,994 --> 00:09:40,294
Did too!

157
00:09:40,429 --> 00:09:42,129
Mama, I
have to pee-pee.

158
00:09:42,130 --> 00:09:43,430
You just did!

159
00:09:43,882 --> 00:09:46,049
If you kids don't stop this,

160
00:09:46,285 --> 00:09:49,037
I'm going to leave you
by the side of the road!

161
00:09:49,038 --> 00:09:51,139
Annie, you just went.
Pipe down.

162
00:09:51,140 --> 00:09:52,640
- Did not!
- Did too.

163
00:09:54,077 --> 00:09:55,611
Pipe down, you two!

164
00:09:55,612 --> 00:09:56,912
Did not!

165
00:09:57,014 --> 00:09:58,514
- Did not!
- Did too.

166
00:09:59,083 --> 00:10:00,984
I'm going to come back there.

167
00:10:00,985 --> 00:10:03,818
You don't want me
to come back there.

168
00:10:04,689 --> 00:10:06,522
Jimmy Johnson, K.I.F.I.

169
00:10:06,624 --> 00:10:08,924
Shayne, leave it for a second.

170
00:10:09,060 --> 00:10:12,129
I'd like to hear just one
song all the way through.

171
00:10:12,130 --> 00:10:13,430
Sorry.

172
00:10:14,300 --> 00:10:16,067
It's my turn up front.

173
00:10:16,202 --> 00:10:17,769
- It is not!
- Is too!

174
00:10:18,570 --> 00:10:20,470
Now don't you two start.

175
00:10:20,689 --> 00:10:22,122
Murray, sit down.

176
00:10:23,310 --> 00:10:24,610
You stink bug.

177
00:10:24,978 --> 00:10:26,045
Is too.

178
00:10:26,046 --> 00:10:27,346
Is not!

179
00:10:27,381 --> 00:10:28,681
Pipe down!

180
00:10:30,650 --> 00:10:32,250
Shayne, how'd you like
to take the wheel?

181
00:10:32,274 --> 00:10:33,419
Sure.

182
00:10:33,554 --> 00:10:34,921
Scoot over here.

183
00:10:41,295 --> 00:10:42,595
Thanks.

184
00:10:43,365 --> 00:10:44,665
Hey...

185
00:10:45,167 --> 00:10:46,484
How about that place?

186
00:10:46,485 --> 00:10:48,585
It looks like a nice place.

187
00:10:48,654 --> 00:10:49,954
Nope.

188
00:10:50,189 --> 00:10:51,590
I want some orange punch.

189
00:10:51,591 --> 00:10:52,891
Why not?

190
00:10:53,760 --> 00:10:55,727
It ain't the right place.

191
00:10:55,812 --> 00:10:57,846
Then, what is the right place?

192
00:10:57,847 --> 00:10:59,481
I'll know it when I see it.

193
00:10:59,482 --> 00:11:00,782
See...

194
00:11:02,453 --> 00:11:04,454
We'll be driving down this road,

195
00:11:04,455 --> 00:11:07,822
and there's going to be
trees on either side.

196
00:11:07,892 --> 00:11:10,227
And we'll go around the curve...

197
00:11:10,228 --> 00:11:11,795
And there it'll be,

198
00:11:12,163 --> 00:11:13,930
a perfect little town.

199
00:11:15,300 --> 00:11:18,533
Then a little further
on will be our house.

200
00:11:19,972 --> 00:11:23,339
Everything will be
buttoned up and beautiful.

201
00:11:24,743 --> 00:11:26,176
Lynn?
Oh, honey.

202
00:11:26,979 --> 00:11:28,479
Are you all right?

203
00:11:28,882 --> 00:11:30,782
Give her
some kool-aid.

204
00:11:32,052 --> 00:11:33,719
Murray did it.
Murray did it.

205
00:11:33,720 --> 00:11:35,153
Don't spit in it.

206
00:11:35,389 --> 00:11:37,056
Shut up, you little fink.

207
00:11:37,057 --> 00:11:38,957
Cut it out.
Cut it out!

208
00:11:42,029 --> 00:11:44,129
Booger eater, booger eater.

209
00:11:46,702 --> 00:11:49,370
Murray, it better not have
come out of your nose.

210
00:11:49,371 --> 00:11:50,671
See it!

211
00:11:50,773 --> 00:11:51,606
Look at that house.

212
00:11:51,607 --> 00:11:52,907
Yeah.

213
00:11:53,909 --> 00:11:56,429
Mama said we would
find us a house this time,

214
00:11:56,430 --> 00:11:59,997
not an apartment,
but a real house, all our own.

215
00:12:00,100 --> 00:12:01,434
We saw lots of possibilities.

216
00:12:01,435 --> 00:12:02,868
Right there. See?

217
00:12:04,304 --> 00:12:05,604
See that deer?

218
00:12:06,174 --> 00:12:09,309
Look at that. Look at all
that space right there!

219
00:12:09,310 --> 00:12:11,077
Perfect for our house.

220
00:12:11,112 --> 00:12:12,412
I want a pony.

221
00:12:13,464 --> 00:12:15,299
Since we were dead broke,

222
00:12:15,300 --> 00:12:17,800
one question kept nagging at me.

223
00:12:17,936 --> 00:12:20,103
Even if we did
find our dream house,

224
00:12:20,104 --> 00:12:22,137
what could we buy it with?

225
00:12:22,273 --> 00:12:24,040
I wish we lived there.

226
00:12:49,054 --> 00:12:50,487
Hurry up, Murray.

227
00:12:50,822 --> 00:12:52,122
Look out!

228
00:12:52,125 --> 00:12:53,425
We've got you.

229
00:12:53,926 --> 00:12:55,226
Take that!

230
00:13:00,332 --> 00:13:02,699
I can patch your radiator here,

231
00:13:02,870 --> 00:13:05,770
but your water pump's gone.
It's shot.

232
00:13:06,390 --> 00:13:09,058
These belts look like they're
about ready to give way.

233
00:13:09,059 --> 00:13:11,428
And there's maybe one
tire in the whole bunch

234
00:13:11,429 --> 00:13:15,129
that'll see you more than
100 yards down the road.

235
00:13:33,336 --> 00:13:34,903
Will this cover it?

236
00:13:36,606 --> 00:13:38,906
Oh, ma'am.
Your wedding ring?

237
00:13:39,610 --> 00:13:41,327
I don't want to take it.

238
00:13:41,328 --> 00:13:43,028
Don't worry about it.

239
00:13:43,397 --> 00:13:46,132
Goddamn vagabond, Irish
Catholic son of a bitch.

240
00:13:46,133 --> 00:13:48,135
Never gave me anything
but grief and kids.

241
00:13:48,136 --> 00:13:50,369
I'm not sentimental about it.

242
00:13:52,057 --> 00:13:55,090
Is it worth enough
to keep my car going?

243
00:13:56,277 --> 00:13:59,710
Lady, this car's worth
more dead than alive...

244
00:13:59,816 --> 00:14:01,916
But I'll do the best I can.

245
00:14:05,604 --> 00:14:08,007
Everyday, for breakfast,
lunch, and dinner,

246
00:14:08,008 --> 00:14:10,175
we ate egg salad sandwiches.

247
00:14:10,377 --> 00:14:13,010
I haven't eaten one since...
Ever.

248
00:14:34,103 --> 00:14:35,604
We drove through 3 states,

249
00:14:35,605 --> 00:14:37,105
one after another.

250
00:14:37,407 --> 00:14:38,974
By the time we reached Idaho,

251
00:14:38,975 --> 00:14:40,808
we'd reached our limits

252
00:14:40,811 --> 00:14:43,145
physically, mentally,
and mechanically.

253
00:14:43,146 --> 00:14:44,447
- Mine!
- Mine!

254
00:14:44,448 --> 00:14:45,748
- Mine!
- Mine!

255
00:14:46,117 --> 00:14:47,550
It's your turn...

256
00:14:47,985 --> 00:14:49,285
I'm not on you!

257
00:14:49,454 --> 00:14:50,754
Shut up!

258
00:14:51,255 --> 00:14:52,622
- Mine!
- Mine!

259
00:14:52,690 --> 00:14:54,457
- Shut up.
- Shut up!

260
00:14:55,694 --> 00:14:56,828
There, I broke one of...

261
00:14:56,829 --> 00:14:58,129
Can it!

262
00:15:01,600 --> 00:15:02,900
What is it?

263
00:15:02,936 --> 00:15:04,236
At first,

264
00:15:04,804 --> 00:15:06,805
I thought
we were out of gas again.

265
00:15:06,806 --> 00:15:08,239
But there it was.

266
00:15:08,842 --> 00:15:10,809
I'm not sure what it was,

267
00:15:11,244 --> 00:15:13,730
but mama had
that look in her eye.

268
00:15:13,731 --> 00:15:16,898
Wherever we were going,
we'd just arrived.

269
00:16:27,229 --> 00:16:28,529
Oh!

270
00:16:28,897 --> 00:16:30,530
Mama, you scared me.

271
00:16:34,519 --> 00:16:35,819
Hey, ma,

272
00:16:35,922 --> 00:16:37,222
come up here.

273
00:16:37,556 --> 00:16:38,440
You can see everything.

274
00:16:38,441 --> 00:16:39,508
Hey, mama.

275
00:16:39,509 --> 00:16:40,809
Hey, mama.

276
00:16:43,046 --> 00:16:44,079
All right.

277
00:16:44,080 --> 00:16:45,649
All right, ok, good.

278
00:16:45,650 --> 00:16:47,184
All right, I got it.

279
00:16:47,185 --> 00:16:48,685
Mom, come up here.

280
00:16:48,952 --> 00:16:50,252
Lynn...

281
00:16:50,454 --> 00:16:52,354
Lynn, no, no, no!
Wait.

282
00:16:54,059 --> 00:16:56,826
Murray, come on.
Let's get this guy.

283
00:16:57,829 --> 00:16:59,129
Lacey tribe,

284
00:16:59,998 --> 00:17:01,298
come on.

285
00:17:17,651 --> 00:17:18,768
Hello?

286
00:17:18,769 --> 00:17:20,069
Hello?

287
00:17:22,373 --> 00:17:23,841
The berries are all done.

288
00:17:23,842 --> 00:17:25,008
No more till next year.

289
00:17:25,009 --> 00:17:26,309
All done.

290
00:17:27,212 --> 00:17:28,512
All done.

291
00:17:28,746 --> 00:17:30,113
We don't want any berries.

292
00:17:30,114 --> 00:17:31,747
I want some berries.

293
00:17:33,452 --> 00:17:35,286
Do you know
who owns that property

294
00:17:35,287 --> 00:17:37,138
across the road from you,

295
00:17:37,139 --> 00:17:40,239
the one with the
tumble-down house on it?

296
00:17:41,811 --> 00:17:43,644
Well...
I'm the owner.

297
00:17:45,849 --> 00:17:47,282
I want to buy it.

298
00:17:54,141 --> 00:17:55,742
My name's Frances Lacey.

299
00:17:55,743 --> 00:17:57,110
That's my tribe.

300
00:17:59,114 --> 00:18:01,315
I'd introduce you to
them one at a time,

301
00:18:01,316 --> 00:18:04,283
but life is short
and time is precious.

302
00:18:09,592 --> 00:18:11,892
I don't know if it's for sale.

303
00:18:16,132 --> 00:18:17,565
I want to buy it.

304
00:18:18,735 --> 00:18:21,437
I want it so bad that I'm in
no position to negotiate.

305
00:18:21,438 --> 00:18:23,198
You can take full advantage.
Name your price.

306
00:18:23,222 --> 00:18:24,522
You rich?

307
00:18:25,542 --> 00:18:27,211
I don't have a pot to piss in

308
00:18:27,212 --> 00:18:29,579
or a window to throw it out of.

309
00:18:53,190 --> 00:18:54,757
I have to pee-pee.

310
00:19:04,670 --> 00:19:06,237
If that's the case,

311
00:19:07,340 --> 00:19:10,240
how do you expect
to pay for the land?

312
00:19:10,309 --> 00:19:11,609
Well, Mr. Moon,

313
00:19:12,010 --> 00:19:14,177
I've learned that the dollar

314
00:19:14,214 --> 00:19:16,574
isn't the only way to get things
done in this great country.

315
00:19:16,598 --> 00:19:17,898
Let's talk.

316
00:19:27,061 --> 00:19:28,561
You live alone,
Mr. Moon?

317
00:19:28,562 --> 00:19:30,697
Yes, if it's any
of your business.

318
00:19:30,698 --> 00:19:32,798
Well, here's what we'll do.

319
00:19:32,935 --> 00:19:34,135
We'll wash your dishes,

320
00:19:34,136 --> 00:19:35,503
do your laundry.

321
00:19:36,171 --> 00:19:38,804
Dishes daily.
Laundry once a week.

322
00:19:39,708 --> 00:19:41,941
Clean your house once a week.

323
00:19:42,712 --> 00:19:45,547
My oldest son will give you eight
hours of chores each week,

324
00:19:45,548 --> 00:19:48,581
plus any other work
you may need on call

325
00:19:48,584 --> 00:19:51,084
at minimum wage plus 10 percent.

326
00:19:51,588 --> 00:19:53,221
You pay me interest?

327
00:19:55,292 --> 00:19:57,193
Mr. Moon, this
is slave labor.

328
00:19:57,194 --> 00:19:58,894
Take advantage of it.

329
00:20:02,367 --> 00:20:03,934
You know something?

330
00:20:05,804 --> 00:20:09,106
I'm not so sure if I want
a smart lady like you

331
00:20:09,107 --> 00:20:11,940
with a bunch of kids
for my neighbor.

332
00:20:15,731 --> 00:20:17,031
Yeah, but...

333
00:20:17,900 --> 00:20:19,467
Look at this place.

334
00:20:20,470 --> 00:20:22,103
Takes a lot of work.

335
00:20:25,191 --> 00:20:26,491
How do I know

336
00:20:27,127 --> 00:20:30,027
you won't just
up and run off someday?

337
00:20:30,732 --> 00:20:32,365
Well, if I did that,

338
00:20:32,901 --> 00:20:35,635
then you'd have all that free
labor plus your land back.

339
00:20:35,636 --> 00:20:37,588
But I'm telling you,
Mr. Moon,

340
00:20:37,589 --> 00:20:39,556
if you sell me that land,

341
00:20:39,824 --> 00:20:42,326
I'm building me and my kids a
house we ain't ever leaving,

342
00:20:42,327 --> 00:20:45,294
at least not while
I'm still breathing.

343
00:20:49,802 --> 00:20:52,171
So mama talked herself
into 3 acres of land

344
00:20:52,172 --> 00:20:54,339
with a half-finished
shack on it,

345
00:20:54,340 --> 00:20:57,440
and we kind of took over
Mr. Moon's life.

346
00:20:57,711 --> 00:21:00,113
Mama negotiated
2 days of free repairs

347
00:21:00,114 --> 00:21:02,414
that ended up lasting 2 weeks.

348
00:21:02,550 --> 00:21:04,650
He never knew what hit him.

349
00:21:04,885 --> 00:21:06,353
We had a lot of work to do.

350
00:21:06,354 --> 00:21:08,122
It was already getting cold.

351
00:21:08,123 --> 00:21:10,524
We had to get
a roof on and walls up...

352
00:21:10,525 --> 00:21:14,092
if you call canvas tarp
a "roof" and old boards,

353
00:21:18,952 --> 00:21:20,585
bye-bye, tumbleweed.

354
00:21:47,699 --> 00:21:48,999
Pull over.

355
00:21:49,368 --> 00:21:50,668
Pull it.

356
00:21:53,073 --> 00:21:54,506
Over. Over. Over.

357
00:21:57,644 --> 00:21:58,878
Turn which way?

358
00:21:58,879 --> 00:22:00,179
This way!

359
00:22:00,180 --> 00:22:01,314
Ok.

360
00:22:01,315 --> 00:22:02,615
Ok.

361
00:22:02,901 --> 00:22:04,001
Hurry, here it comes.

362
00:22:04,002 --> 00:22:05,302
Here it comes!

363
00:22:10,308 --> 00:22:11,608
Aah!

364
00:22:13,512 --> 00:22:14,612
I'm going to get you!

365
00:22:14,613 --> 00:22:15,913
Aah!

366
00:22:15,948 --> 00:22:17,248
Aah!

367
00:22:17,449 --> 00:22:18,749
Wait up, pals.

368
00:22:18,817 --> 00:22:20,117
Come on!

369
00:22:29,864 --> 00:22:31,164
Here, Faye.

370
00:22:46,848 --> 00:22:48,148
Yay! Yay! Yay!

371
00:22:48,785 --> 00:22:50,085
- Yes!
- Yeah!

372
00:22:51,604 --> 00:22:54,704
Mama traded our tires
for some furniture.

373
00:22:54,841 --> 00:22:57,577
Mr. Moon wanted the name of
the guy who bought them.

374
00:22:57,578 --> 00:23:02,011
He said he wanted proof that he
wasn't the only fool in town.

375
00:23:11,276 --> 00:23:12,609
So what do you know how to do?

376
00:23:12,610 --> 00:23:13,910
I work.

377
00:23:14,746 --> 00:23:17,313
I've done it all my life.
I work.

378
00:23:17,783 --> 00:23:20,883
I learn fast, and I
do my share and more.

379
00:23:21,287 --> 00:23:23,187
Yeah, well, I do need
another waitress.

380
00:23:23,188 --> 00:23:24,621
Then you got one.

381
00:23:32,165 --> 00:23:33,465
Minimum wage.

382
00:23:33,767 --> 00:23:35,302
Your tips are your own,

383
00:23:35,303 --> 00:23:37,270
and they ain't
much in this town.

384
00:23:37,271 --> 00:23:39,304
I'll manage.
I always do.

385
00:23:39,407 --> 00:23:40,774
I'll bet you do.

386
00:23:42,943 --> 00:23:45,012
This here's Norman, my manager.

387
00:23:45,013 --> 00:23:47,113
You'll be working under me.

388
00:23:47,949 --> 00:23:49,849
I'll be working for you.

389
00:23:54,924 --> 00:23:56,224
Frances.

390
00:23:57,560 --> 00:23:58,860
Frances.

391
00:24:03,918 --> 00:24:05,885
I tried to get any job I could.

392
00:24:05,886 --> 00:24:07,453
I wasn't particular

393
00:24:07,555 --> 00:24:09,722
as long as I could make money.

394
00:24:09,723 --> 00:24:12,023
I finally got work at a dairy.

395
00:24:14,028 --> 00:24:15,395
I don't know
who hated it more...

396
00:24:15,396 --> 00:24:16,696
me or the cows.

397
00:24:20,134 --> 00:24:22,471
This dumb blanket won't stay up.

398
00:24:22,472 --> 00:24:24,039
I already got some.

399
00:24:28,911 --> 00:24:30,611
Give me a hand, Lynn.

400
00:24:34,084 --> 00:24:36,184
Hey, hey,
Mr. Moon's here!

401
00:24:38,121 --> 00:24:39,421
Thanks.

402
00:24:41,058 --> 00:24:43,293
What are you up to,
Mr. Moon?

403
00:24:43,294 --> 00:24:44,495
You see...

404
00:24:44,496 --> 00:24:45,796
I had all this

405
00:24:46,263 --> 00:24:47,830
spare window glass.

406
00:24:58,327 --> 00:25:01,694
A man with a greenhouse
keeps plenty on hand.

407
00:25:02,549 --> 00:25:04,516
I used some of your wood.

408
00:25:07,788 --> 00:25:09,088
Glazed windows.

409
00:25:11,058 --> 00:25:13,625
And now I'm ready
to put them in.

410
00:25:18,066 --> 00:25:21,966
I don't have the money to
pay you for this, Mr. Moon.

411
00:25:22,404 --> 00:25:23,704
Well...

412
00:25:25,374 --> 00:25:26,874
I'm not doing this

413
00:25:27,093 --> 00:25:29,193
for the money,
Mrs. Lacey.

414
00:25:31,563 --> 00:25:32,930
I do well enough

415
00:25:33,666 --> 00:25:35,099
with the nursery.

416
00:25:38,071 --> 00:25:40,372
Well, I want an
accounting of your time

417
00:25:40,373 --> 00:25:42,074
and the cost of your materials

418
00:25:42,075 --> 00:25:44,242
so I can give
you an I.O.U.

419
00:25:44,745 --> 00:25:46,346
I don't like owing anybody,

420
00:25:46,347 --> 00:25:48,282
but you backed me into a corner.

421
00:25:48,283 --> 00:25:50,583
And I'd appreciate
it a hell of a lot

422
00:25:50,584 --> 00:25:54,551
if you'd let me know next
time you decide to help out.

423
00:26:20,284 --> 00:26:21,584
Come on.

424
00:26:22,337 --> 00:26:24,338
Mama had promised
I'd do Mr. Moon's chores,

425
00:26:24,339 --> 00:26:25,974
so I didn't have much choice.

426
00:26:25,975 --> 00:26:28,309
But running his tractor was fun,

427
00:26:28,310 --> 00:26:30,943
and that's how
I learned to drive.

428
00:26:44,495 --> 00:26:45,595
Hi.

429
00:26:45,596 --> 00:26:46,896
Hello.

430
00:26:48,666 --> 00:26:50,699
How does that look, Craig?

431
00:26:52,270 --> 00:26:53,570
Pretty good.

432
00:27:00,246 --> 00:27:02,080
Let's sleep on the roof.

433
00:27:02,081 --> 00:27:03,348
I want that room.

434
00:27:03,349 --> 00:27:05,516
You can't sleep on the roof!

435
00:27:05,551 --> 00:27:07,819
Mom, can I have my own bathroom?

436
00:27:07,820 --> 00:27:09,722
Can I have a pink
princess phone?

437
00:27:09,723 --> 00:27:12,223
Mom, can I have my own bathroom?

438
00:27:12,726 --> 00:27:14,426
School was coming up,

439
00:27:14,561 --> 00:27:16,696
so when the hand-me-downs
wore out,

440
00:27:16,697 --> 00:27:18,999
the church basement
was our department store.

441
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:20,400
This wasn't so bad.

442
00:27:20,401 --> 00:27:21,968
It was all we knew.

443
00:27:35,034 --> 00:27:36,934
Lynn, what do you think?

444
00:27:38,104 --> 00:27:39,404
It's beautiful.

445
00:27:39,572 --> 00:27:41,072
You should get it.

446
00:27:41,141 --> 00:27:42,441
Mama.

447
00:27:42,842 --> 00:27:44,142
Oh, no, honey.

448
00:27:44,277 --> 00:27:45,577
Annie.

449
00:27:48,700 --> 00:27:50,000
Lacey tribe.

450
00:27:51,936 --> 00:27:54,103
We need galoshes for winter.

451
00:27:54,873 --> 00:27:55,473
You've never seen winter,
have you, Annie?

452
00:27:55,474 --> 00:27:56,774
No.

453
00:27:57,242 --> 00:27:59,609
Help her pick out a pair, Lynn.

454
00:28:00,579 --> 00:28:01,879
Craig.

455
00:28:05,918 --> 00:28:07,418
Here. Try this on.

456
00:28:07,454 --> 00:28:08,754
Mom, look!

457
00:28:11,123 --> 00:28:12,490
Good day, ma'am.

458
00:28:12,959 --> 00:28:14,726
Uh, I'm Father Tomlin.

459
00:28:15,730 --> 00:28:17,831
I think you may be new
to our little town.

460
00:28:17,832 --> 00:28:19,465
Mom, look what I found.

461
00:28:19,466 --> 00:28:21,601
Hope that we'll see you
at Sunday mass soon.

462
00:28:21,602 --> 00:28:23,235
Try again, liberace.

463
00:28:24,873 --> 00:28:26,673
Unless, of course,
your convictions

464
00:28:26,674 --> 00:28:28,542
take you to another church.

465
00:28:28,543 --> 00:28:31,445
Actually, we Laceys
are nondenominational.

466
00:28:31,446 --> 00:28:33,581
Well, that's neither here
nor there at the moment,

467
00:28:33,582 --> 00:28:35,283
but perhaps I could tell you

468
00:28:35,284 --> 00:28:38,051
about our program
to help the needy.

469
00:28:38,287 --> 00:28:40,520
We can provide without charge

470
00:28:40,556 --> 00:28:42,992
an allotment of clothing for
each member of the family...

471
00:28:42,993 --> 00:28:45,128
Murray, we didn't come here
looking for toys.

472
00:28:45,129 --> 00:28:48,096
Come back here
and try on this sweater.

473
00:28:48,632 --> 00:28:51,368
Uh, in addition to the clothing
items, basic food items...

474
00:28:51,369 --> 00:28:52,669
mama, look!

475
00:28:53,437 --> 00:28:54,737
Lynn, no.

476
00:28:58,076 --> 00:29:00,443
Uh, basic food items and so on,

477
00:29:01,346 --> 00:29:02,847
all without obligation,

478
00:29:02,848 --> 00:29:04,582
religious or otherwise.

479
00:29:04,583 --> 00:29:07,950
Well, thanks very much,
mister, uh... Father,

480
00:29:08,254 --> 00:29:10,355
but we Laceys
don't accept charity.

481
00:29:10,356 --> 00:29:11,923
We pay our own way.

482
00:29:12,392 --> 00:29:13,692
Well, uh,

483
00:29:14,394 --> 00:29:16,894
if... if you
change your mind...

484
00:29:23,037 --> 00:29:24,337
Lynn.

485
00:29:28,576 --> 00:29:30,845
Do me a favor. Take
this back, will you?

486
00:29:30,846 --> 00:29:32,213
But it'll look so nice on you.

487
00:29:32,214 --> 00:29:33,514
Take it back.

488
00:29:37,787 --> 00:29:39,354
The really bad part

489
00:29:39,856 --> 00:29:43,556
was when mama decided
to make our clothes herself.

490
00:29:52,919 --> 00:29:55,555
Hey, Lacey, where'd you get
the howdy doody dresses?

491
00:29:55,556 --> 00:29:57,157
They're not howdy doody.

492
00:29:57,158 --> 00:29:58,658
My mama made them.

493
00:29:59,160 --> 00:30:01,061
Where'd she get the material?

494
00:30:01,062 --> 00:30:03,464
Did somebody shoot a
sofa and skin it?

495
00:30:03,465 --> 00:30:05,232
"Howdy doody dresses"

496
00:30:05,651 --> 00:30:07,418
"howdy doody dresses"

497
00:30:48,765 --> 00:30:51,366
Murray still didn't seem
to fit into our world,

498
00:30:51,367 --> 00:30:52,800
but then one day,

499
00:30:52,903 --> 00:30:54,803
he found one of his own.

500
00:30:55,305 --> 00:30:56,605
Stop the bus!

501
00:30:56,790 --> 00:30:58,825
Stop the bus.
Stop the bus!

502
00:30:58,826 --> 00:31:00,126
Stop the bus.

503
00:31:00,461 --> 00:31:02,561
Get back in your seat, kid.

504
00:31:03,365 --> 00:31:04,665
Stop the bus,

505
00:31:04,766 --> 00:31:06,467
or I'll barf in your hat.

506
00:31:06,468 --> 00:31:07,768
Eew! Eew! Eew!

507
00:31:14,110 --> 00:31:15,410
I'll walk home.

508
00:32:24,737 --> 00:32:26,037
You lost, boy?

509
00:32:26,673 --> 00:32:27,973
No.

510
00:32:29,810 --> 00:32:31,110
No.

511
00:32:32,646 --> 00:32:34,679
I want some of this stuff.

512
00:32:39,187 --> 00:32:40,487
You got money?

513
00:32:41,356 --> 00:32:42,656
Mmm. No.

514
00:32:43,926 --> 00:32:45,493
Well, how do you expect to pay

515
00:32:45,494 --> 00:32:47,262
for the stuff you want?

516
00:32:47,263 --> 00:32:48,563
Well, mister,

517
00:32:49,365 --> 00:32:50,998
I've learned that...

518
00:32:51,016 --> 00:32:52,316
I've learned...

519
00:32:53,554 --> 00:32:55,955
That the greenback dollar
isn't the only way

520
00:32:55,956 --> 00:32:59,325
to get things done
in this here great country.

521
00:32:59,326 --> 00:33:00,626
Let's talk.

522
00:33:12,291 --> 00:33:13,591
All right, son.

523
00:33:17,363 --> 00:33:19,097
Let's find this stuff you want.

524
00:33:19,098 --> 00:33:20,998
I need help around here.

525
00:33:30,645 --> 00:33:31,945
Murray!

526
00:33:34,314 --> 00:33:35,682
What's with the wagon,

527
00:33:35,683 --> 00:33:37,417
and what's with the toilet?

528
00:33:37,418 --> 00:33:39,085
I got a job.
I earned it.

529
00:33:39,086 --> 00:33:40,755
Come on, give me a hand.

530
00:33:40,756 --> 00:33:43,223
You got a job, and
you earned a toilet?

531
00:33:43,224 --> 00:33:46,260
Yeah. So we don't have to
use the dumb old outhouse.

532
00:33:46,261 --> 00:33:47,894
I hate the outhouse.

533
00:33:49,632 --> 00:33:51,599
So for 3 days every week,

534
00:33:51,901 --> 00:33:55,103
Murray came home hauling some
new treasures from Mr. king.

535
00:33:55,104 --> 00:33:56,872
We never knew what to expect...

536
00:33:56,873 --> 00:33:58,906
French doors, a gas stove,

537
00:33:59,476 --> 00:34:01,811
a set of cracked China dishes...

538
00:34:01,812 --> 00:34:03,712
In smelly old
Mr. king,

539
00:34:03,714 --> 00:34:05,682
Murray found a kindred soul,

540
00:34:05,683 --> 00:34:07,916
a fellow connoisseur of junk.

541
00:34:12,090 --> 00:34:13,390
Come on.

542
00:34:13,424 --> 00:34:14,991
Come on what is it?

