576
00:37:26,405 --> 00:37:27,772
Murray, come on.

577
00:37:29,541 --> 00:37:31,641
- Come on.
- Look, Shayne!

578
00:37:31,910 --> 00:37:33,210
Shayne, look!

579
00:37:33,380 --> 00:37:34,680
Look, Shayne!

580
00:37:34,764 --> 00:37:36,064
Shayne, look!

581
00:37:36,099 --> 00:37:37,399
What?

582
00:37:43,291 --> 00:37:44,958
Hold on.
This is going to hurt.

583
00:37:44,959 --> 00:37:47,192
It's going to hurt all right.

584
00:37:56,471 --> 00:37:57,771
Ow!

585
00:38:01,644 --> 00:38:03,411
It should be all right.

586
00:38:03,412 --> 00:38:05,045
You'll be all right.

587
00:38:06,799 --> 00:38:08,499
I'm getting Mr. Moon.

588
00:38:19,081 --> 00:38:20,380
It's all right.

589
00:38:20,381 --> 00:38:21,881
Don't die, Murray.

590
00:38:26,021 --> 00:38:27,321
Stay here.

591
00:38:33,896 --> 00:38:36,231
But Mr. Moon wasn't
home to help us.

592
00:38:36,232 --> 00:38:38,067
He had driven mama into town.

593
00:38:38,068 --> 00:38:40,536
I had to carry Murray
to the hospital.

594
00:38:40,537 --> 00:38:42,570
He was crying all the way.

595
00:39:15,059 --> 00:39:16,159
What the hell happened?

596
00:39:16,160 --> 00:39:17,594
Get him in the truck.

597
00:39:17,595 --> 00:39:19,296
It's not my fault, mama.

598
00:39:19,297 --> 00:39:22,130
He fell on a nail,
and he's bleeding.

599
00:39:32,461 --> 00:39:34,696
Dr. Bartlett, you're needed
in room two.

600
00:39:34,697 --> 00:39:35,664
Mrs. Lacey.

601
00:39:35,665 --> 00:39:36,965
Yes.

602
00:39:38,401 --> 00:39:40,968
You have a very
lucky little boy.

603
00:39:41,671 --> 00:39:44,238
