00:51:22,214 --> 00:51:24,848
This Christmas, we don't need
to get each other presents.

808
00:51:24,849 --> 00:51:26,884
We'll get presents
for our house.

809
00:51:26,885 --> 00:51:28,385
Like a television?

810
00:51:29,120 --> 00:51:31,222
Well, maybe not like a
great big old television.

811
00:51:31,223 --> 00:51:32,656
What about Santa?

812
00:51:33,058 --> 00:51:35,894
Well, he'll get presents
for our house, too.

813
00:51:35,895 --> 00:51:37,595
Can Santa bring a TV?

814
00:51:38,146 --> 00:51:39,779
It's too big, dummy.

815
00:51:40,650 --> 00:51:42,817
Shut up, Annie. I want a TV.

816
00:51:43,987 --> 00:51:45,487
What do you think?

817
00:51:46,022 --> 00:51:47,389
It's ok with me.

818
00:51:47,957 --> 00:51:50,590
- I like the idea.
- Fine with me.

819
00:51:51,496 --> 00:51:52,996
What do you think?

820
00:51:54,098 --> 00:51:54,931
Sure.

821
00:51:54,932 --> 00:51:56,232
Huh?

822
00:51:56,401 --> 00:51:58,101
Sure.
You were late.

823
00:51:59,204 --> 00:52:00,504
What?

824
00:52:01,139 --> 00:52:03,307
I said you were late.
Where were you?

825
00:52:03,308 --> 00:52:04,808
I went for a beer.

826
00:52:05,310 --> 00:52:06,610
Really?

827
00:52:06,645 --> 00:52:07,945
With Norm?

828
00:52:10,016 --> 00:52:11,316
Yes, with Norm.

829
00:52:23,764 --> 00:52:25,197
You listen to me.

830
00:52:26,067 --> 00:52:28,502
You leave my private life
to me, Shayne Patrick,

831
00:52:28,503 --> 00:52:30,470
what little I have of it.

832
00:52:33,875 --> 00:52:35,577
This weekend we get the tree!

833
00:52:35,578 --> 00:52:36,878
Yay! Yay! Yay!

834
00:52:41,884 --> 00:52:43,852
When you're really, really poor,

835
00:52:43,853 --> 00:52:45,353
everything you see

836
00:52:45,622 --> 00:52:47,789
is something you can't have.

837
00:52:51,161 --> 00:52:52,461
- Shayne?
- Yeah.

838
00:52:53,465 --> 00:52:55,231
What are you going to
get mama for Christmas?

839
00:52:55,232 --> 00:52:56,532
I don't know.

840
00:52:57,502 --> 00:52:59,202
Maybe some stockings.

841
00:53:02,039 --> 00:53:05,142
I saw her crying last night
when she ruined her last pair.

842
00:53:05,143 --> 00:53:09,310
I thought we were supposed to
get presents for our house.

843
00:53:09,949 --> 00:53:12,182
That's just talk, that's all.

844
00:53:12,418 --> 00:53:13,718
You sure?

845
00:53:13,887 --> 00:53:15,788
We wrote that letter to Santa.

846
00:53:15,789 --> 00:53:18,556
Yeah. You know
how mom always talks.

847
00:53:19,258 --> 00:53:20,618
Does that mean
I get a Bowie knife?

848
00:53:20,642 --> 00:53:21,942
No.

849
00:53:27,618 --> 00:53:29,752
Coming through.
Coming through.

850
00:53:29,753 --> 00:53:31,053
Step aside.

851
00:53:31,256 --> 00:53:32,556
Thanks.

852
00:53:35,793 --> 00:53:37,093
Wait, wait.

853
00:53:44,553 --> 00:53:46,254
When I was a kid,
we had an old bathtub.

854
00:53:46,255 --> 00:53:47,555
It was so big,

855
00:53:47,706 --> 00:53:49,542
I could lay down up to my chin.

856
00:53:49,543 --> 00:53:51,377
My knees would
still be underwater.

857
00:53:51,378 --> 00:53:52,945
I'd read for hours.

858
00:53:53,380 --> 00:53:55,848
The books would get all fat and
crinkly from the dampness.

859
00:53:55,849 --> 00:53:57,983
Did you live in
a house of your own?

860
00:53:57,984 --> 00:54:00,417
Yeah. Lived there
until I left.

861
00:54:01,889 --> 00:54:04,458
How's Santa going to come
if we don't have a chimbly?

862
00:54:04,459 --> 00:54:05,759
It's chimney.

863
00:54:06,861 --> 00:54:08,930
He'll have to come
through the keyhole,

864
00:54:08,931 --> 00:54:10,598
like he did in Los Angeles.

865
00:54:10,599 --> 00:54:12,133
- Dummy!
- You're the dummy!

866
00:54:12,134 --> 00:54:13,168
Dummy!
You are.

867
00:54:13,169 --> 00:54:14,469
No, you are.

868
00:54:17,073 --> 00:54:19,007
The water's getting all gunky.

869
00:54:19,008 --> 00:54:20,441
Look who's in it.

870
00:54:21,511 --> 00:54:24,278
Why am I always last
to take a bath?

871
00:54:24,414 --> 00:54:27,317
'Cause nobody wants to wash
after you've been in there.

872
00:54:27,318 --> 00:54:28,618
Well, I'm done.

873
00:54:29,753 --> 00:54:31,586
Not so fast, young man.

874
00:54:33,124 --> 00:54:34,424
Let me see those ears.

875
00:54:34,425 --> 00:54:35,725
I cleaned them.

876
00:54:36,695 --> 00:54:39,630
Oh, Murray. You could
plant potatoes in there.

877
00:54:39,631 --> 00:54:40,931
Ouch!

878
00:54:41,433 --> 00:54:44,933
Oh, I'm sorry. Did I hurt you?
I'm sorry, baby.

879
00:54:45,505 --> 00:54:49,872
You're getting to be an independent
little snot, aren't you?

880
00:54:55,966 --> 00:54:57,867
Hello again,
Mrs. Lacey.

881
00:54:57,868 --> 00:54:59,168
Every year,

882
00:54:59,302 --> 00:55:00,670
we pass out these presents

883
00:55:00,671 --> 00:55:02,372
to the needy children...

884
00:55:02,373 --> 00:55:04,307
needy children?
Good for you Father!

885
00:55:04,308 --> 00:55:07,277
I suggest you find some.
There's none here.

886
00:55:07,278 --> 00:55:09,880
I'm sure your children would
appreciate some gesture...

887
00:55:09,881 --> 00:55:12,416
my children's gifts
are already under the tree.

888
00:55:12,417 --> 00:55:15,184
Merry Christmas.
Good night, Father.

889
00:55:16,789 --> 00:55:18,890
Let's get ready for bed.
Santa's almost here.

890
00:55:18,891 --> 00:55:20,324
Yeah! Yeah! Yeah!

891
00:55:34,842 --> 00:55:36,809
Murray, look! Santa came!

892
00:55:37,645 --> 00:55:39,145
Santa drank the milk!

893
00:55:39,146 --> 00:55:40,579
Look! Look! Look!

894
00:55:40,681 --> 00:55:41,981
Santa came!

895
00:55:43,719 --> 00:55:45,019
Come on!

896
00:55:46,087 --> 00:55:48,088
- Presents!
- I saw them! No!

897
00:55:48,089 --> 00:55:50,224
Stop it. We have to
wake up mom first.

898
00:55:50,225 --> 00:55:51,525
Come on.

899
00:55:51,628 --> 00:55:52,928
Mom! Mom! Mom!

900
00:55:53,430 --> 00:55:54,730
Ok! Ok!

901
00:55:55,231 --> 00:55:56,531
Mom! Mom! Mom!

902
00:56:02,807 --> 00:56:04,107
Where's mine?

903
00:56:04,608 --> 00:56:07,175
Yeah, where's mine?
Where's mine?

904
00:56:07,411 --> 00:56:08,711
Oh! Santa came!

905
00:56:11,483 --> 00:56:13,050
Here. I found mine.

906
00:56:17,956 --> 00:56:19,256
Oh, Lynn.

907
00:56:21,060 --> 00:56:22,360
Thanks.

908
00:56:22,695 --> 00:56:24,995
I wonder why this is so heavy.

909
00:56:28,234 --> 00:56:29,534
Ready?

910
00:56:30,003 --> 00:56:31,303
One...

911
00:56:32,339 --> 00:56:33,639
Two...

912
00:56:33,941 --> 00:56:35,241
Three!

913
00:56:36,209 --> 00:56:37,509
Save the paper.

914
00:56:38,613 --> 00:56:39,913
Why?

915
00:56:44,052 --> 00:56:46,085
I bet I know what this is.

916
00:57:17,255 --> 00:57:18,555
Oh, Lynn!

917
00:57:21,593 --> 00:57:23,760
Did you make these yourself?

918
00:57:42,768 --> 00:57:44,068
What's wrong?

919
00:57:49,041 --> 00:57:51,275
They're presents for our house.

920
00:57:51,276 --> 00:57:53,576
Remember?
We talked about it.

921
00:57:58,000 --> 00:57:59,633
This is not a house.

922
00:58:07,477 --> 00:58:09,244
This is not Christmas.

923
00:58:12,717 --> 00:58:14,284
We live in a shack.

924
00:58:15,720 --> 00:58:17,020
A shack!

925
00:58:18,423 --> 00:58:20,523
We have nothing of our own.

926
00:58:22,444 --> 00:58:25,680
Everything we did have, we either
sold it or left it behind...

927
00:58:25,681 --> 00:58:27,048
we have nothing!

928
00:58:27,416 --> 00:58:29,318
It's supposed to be
Christmas, goddamn it!

929
00:58:29,319 --> 00:58:30,619
It's Christmas!

930
00:58:31,121 --> 00:58:34,354
You watch your mouth,
Shayne Patrick Lacey.

931
00:58:35,158 --> 00:58:37,058
Well, I like what I got.

932
00:58:40,014 --> 00:58:42,914
All that money we earned,
and nothing.

933
00:58:45,620 --> 00:58:48,122
You're mad 'cause you didn't
get a stupid t-shirt.

934
00:58:48,123 --> 00:58:49,490
Shut up, Murray!

935
00:58:52,928 --> 00:58:55,262
All they wanted was
some toys or a radio...

936
00:58:55,263 --> 00:58:56,563
you know what?

937
00:58:57,399 --> 00:59:01,903
You care more about this stupid
shack or this stupid house idea

938
00:59:01,904 --> 00:59:04,071
than you do about any of us!

939
00:59:10,547 --> 00:59:12,580
Go get your father's belt.

940
00:59:17,889 --> 00:59:19,189
Go get it.

941
00:59:49,474 --> 00:59:50,774
I'll get it.

942
00:59:54,580 --> 00:59:56,280
Ooh. Merry Christmas.

943
00:59:57,015 --> 00:59:58,448
I was going to...

944
01:00:03,257 --> 01:00:05,357
Merry Christmas,
Mr. Moon.

945
01:00:20,909 --> 01:00:23,544
I know you had told me
not to bring any presents,

946
01:00:23,545 --> 01:00:24,845
but...

947
01:00:25,481 --> 01:00:27,248
This is for the house.

948
01:00:32,855 --> 01:00:35,555
Uh, Lynn,
get Mr. Moon his present.

949
01:00:37,844 --> 01:00:39,144
It's a mailbox.

950
01:00:42,917 --> 01:00:45,018
We got the spelling off
the contract,

951
01:00:45,019 --> 01:00:47,586
and Shayne made it
in shop class.

952
01:00:47,588 --> 01:00:48,888
Yes. Thank you.

953
01:00:52,727 --> 01:00:54,027
What is this?

954
01:00:54,162 --> 01:00:55,462
Plans.

955
01:00:57,266 --> 01:00:59,935
The blueprints for
the rest of this house.

956
01:00:59,936 --> 01:01:02,036
It's not like your picture.

957
01:01:02,104 --> 01:01:04,172
It's one-story ranch
with 2 bedrooms,

958
01:01:04,173 --> 01:01:05,874
but that can be changed.

959
01:01:05,875 --> 01:01:07,775
It's a good, solid plan.

960
01:01:16,671 --> 01:01:19,238
I really appreciate it,
Mr. Moon,

961
01:01:20,074 --> 01:01:23,107
but we're set on
building our own house.

962
01:01:23,812 --> 01:01:25,179
Merry Christmas.

963
01:01:31,187 --> 01:01:32,487
You...

964
01:01:33,989 --> 01:01:36,556
Are a stubborn woman,
Mrs. Lacey.

965
01:01:48,439 --> 01:01:50,139
What's wrong in here?

966
01:01:52,043 --> 01:01:53,743
Santa Claus hates me.

967
01:02:02,672 --> 01:02:03,972
Mr. Moon...

968
01:02:06,475 --> 01:02:07,843
Could you give me
a ride into town?

969
01:02:07,844 --> 01:02:09,144
Yes, ma'am.

970
01:02:09,345 --> 01:02:11,378
I'll be ready in a minute.

971
01:02:12,049 --> 01:02:14,282
I'll be warming up the truck.

972
01:02:32,905 --> 01:02:34,272
Merry Christmas.

973
01:02:35,107 --> 01:02:37,807
- Happy new year.
- Happy new year.

974
01:02:39,611 --> 01:02:41,244
Thank you very much,

975
01:02:41,281 --> 01:02:43,514
and a Merry Christmas to you.

976
01:02:44,651 --> 01:02:46,068
Excuse me, Father.

977
01:02:46,069 --> 01:02:47,369
Oh, Mrs. Lacey.

978
01:02:47,838 --> 01:02:49,639
I certainly didn't
expect to see you here.

979
01:02:49,640 --> 01:02:51,473
Well, actually, Father,

980
01:02:51,642 --> 01:02:54,477
I was hoping to take you up
on your offer.

981
01:02:54,478 --> 01:02:57,147
Would you have any
of those presents left?

982
01:02:57,148 --> 01:02:58,981
Uh, I took your advice.

983
01:02:59,084 --> 01:03:01,851
I gave them
to a truly needy family.

984
01:03:02,021 --> 01:03:03,721
So you have no gifts?

985
01:03:04,589 --> 01:03:05,889
You know,

986
01:03:06,292 --> 01:03:08,360
the best gift
that you could give them,

987
01:03:08,361 --> 01:03:11,528
would be to bring them
all here to church.

988
01:03:12,699 --> 01:03:14,749
Father Tomlin,
that was wonderful.

989
01:03:14,750 --> 01:03:16,785
Thank you. I greatly
enjoyed that sermon.

990
01:03:16,786 --> 01:03:18,753
I have money.
I can pay.

991
01:03:18,855 --> 01:03:20,656
I'm... I'm sorry,
Mrs. Lacey.

992
01:03:20,657 --> 01:03:23,024
We... we have none.
I'm sorry.

993
01:03:41,614 --> 01:03:43,714
Is it warm enough in there?

994
01:03:44,217 --> 01:03:45,517
Warm enough.

995
01:03:46,853 --> 01:03:50,353
Why didn't you finish
this place, Mr. Munimura?

996
01:03:50,624 --> 01:03:52,524
I started it for my boy.

997
01:03:53,293 --> 01:03:55,060
He went into the Navy.

998
01:03:55,363 --> 01:03:56,796
He was a pilot...

999
01:03:56,897 --> 01:03:58,197
Flew jet.

1000
01:04:00,118 --> 01:04:03,218
Married a nice Japanese
girl from Hawaii.

1001
01:04:04,056 --> 01:04:05,657
They were going to move here

1002
01:04:05,658 --> 01:04:07,691
after their tour in Korea.

1003
01:04:08,027 --> 01:04:09,460
Munimura and son.

1004
01:04:13,066 --> 01:04:14,366
Korea...

1005
01:04:16,336 --> 01:04:17,903
He wanted to fight.

1006
01:04:19,406 --> 01:04:21,239
Michael wanted to prove

1007
01:04:21,374 --> 01:04:24,007
he was as American
as anyone else.

1008
01:04:24,579 --> 01:04:27,079
Chieko and I started this place.

1009
01:04:27,782 --> 01:04:30,082
It was going to be a surprise.

1010
01:04:31,218 --> 01:04:32,851
He didn't come back.

1011
01:04:33,722 --> 01:04:36,089
His wife went on with her life.

1012
01:04:36,625 --> 01:04:38,658
Chieko died the next year.

1013
01:04:47,704 --> 01:04:49,471
I'm sorry about the blueprints.

1014
01:04:49,472 --> 01:04:50,941
I shouldn't have said that.

1015
01:04:50,942 --> 01:04:53,042
I didn't even look at them.

1016
01:04:53,844 --> 01:04:55,144
No, no.

1017
01:04:55,479 --> 01:04:58,347
You have a right
to your kind of house.

1018
01:04:58,348 --> 01:05:00,250
Chieko and I started this place

1019
01:05:00,251 --> 01:05:03,018
so there'd be a family
someday here.

1020
01:05:03,989 --> 01:05:06,857
You and your tribe are
more than Chieko hoped for

1021
01:05:06,858 --> 01:05:09,491
as far as the number
is concerned,

1022
01:05:10,563 --> 01:05:13,632
but you saw something here
the day you drove up

1023
01:05:13,633 --> 01:05:15,800
in that rattletrap Plymouth.

1024
01:05:16,869 --> 01:05:18,902
Don't forget what you saw.

1025
01:05:28,382 --> 01:05:30,749
Merry Christmas,
Mr. Munimura.

1026
01:05:33,655 --> 01:05:35,888
Merry Christmas,
Mrs. Lacey.

1027
01:05:58,732 --> 01:06:00,032
Mama...

1028
01:06:01,002 --> 01:06:03,069
You didn't open the rest
of your presents.

1029
01:06:03,070 --> 01:06:04,370
Tomorrow.

1030
01:06:04,506 --> 01:06:06,206
Mama, come over here.

1031
01:06:06,408 --> 01:06:07,841
I got to finish the dishes.

1032
01:06:07,842 --> 01:06:10,409
Come on.
No, I mean it. I got to.

1033
01:06:22,392 --> 01:06:23,959
Oh, good. They fit.

1034
01:06:23,994 --> 01:06:25,294
Oh, good.

1035
01:06:28,665 --> 01:06:30,432
Oh, God, I'm so tired.

1036
01:06:34,239 --> 01:06:36,072
I'm just so damn tired.

1037
01:06:38,709 --> 01:06:41,409
W-well, maybe
you should go to bed.

1038
01:06:46,152 --> 01:06:48,319
It's not that kind of tired.

1039
01:06:51,558 --> 01:06:54,058
Sometimes I don't think I can...

1040
01:06:58,999 --> 01:07:00,499
I feel like I'm...

1041
01:07:01,369 --> 01:07:03,202
Pushing a car uphill...

1042
01:07:04,505 --> 01:07:06,639
a... a big car
like our Plymouth...

1043
01:07:06,640 --> 01:07:08,007
up a steep hill,

1044
01:07:08,242 --> 01:07:10,278
and I'm... I'm pushing
and pushing,

1045
01:07:10,279 --> 01:07:12,979
and... and I push,
and I look down,

1046
01:07:13,015 --> 01:07:15,083
and I can see
the ground under my feet,

1047
01:07:15,084 --> 01:07:17,185
and then I look up,
and I can see all you,

1048
01:07:17,186 --> 01:07:18,988
kids in the back seat.
Looking at me,

1049
01:07:18,989 --> 01:07:20,956
and... and I'm pushing...

1050
01:07:25,195 --> 01:07:27,628
But, mama, we're not in the car.

1051
01:07:29,066 --> 01:07:30,899
We're helping you push.

1052
01:07:33,670 --> 01:07:34,970
Yeah.

1053
01:07:37,108 --> 01:07:38,408
Yeah, you are.

1054
01:07:40,312 --> 01:07:41,679
Of course, mama.

1055
01:07:41,813 --> 01:07:43,580
We're the Lacey tribe.

1056
01:07:45,217 --> 01:07:48,917
It just feels like you're
pushing alone sometimes.

1057
01:07:50,390 --> 01:07:51,656
Here.

1058
01:07:51,657 --> 01:07:53,157
You open this one.

1059
01:08:11,396 --> 01:08:13,563
That's from Annie and Craig.

1060
01:08:14,232 --> 01:08:16,465
We helped, but just a little.

1061
01:08:40,478 --> 01:08:41,778
Look at that.

1062
01:08:43,215 --> 01:08:45,315
It was a long, long winter.

1063
01:08:46,251 --> 01:08:48,618
Mama and I were still fighting,

1064
01:08:48,754 --> 01:08:51,623
and being cooped up
in that shack didn't help.

1065
01:08:51,624 --> 01:08:53,458
There wasn't anything to do

1066
01:08:53,459 --> 01:08:54,959
or anywhere to go.

1067
01:09:19,704 --> 01:09:20,839
I like that one.

1068
01:09:20,840 --> 01:09:22,873
That's mine.
That's mine.

1069
01:09:23,576 --> 01:09:24,475
Look at that.

1070
01:09:24,476 --> 01:09:25,544
That looks...

1071
01:09:25,545 --> 01:09:26,912
oh! Look at that one.

1072
01:09:26,913 --> 01:09:28,213
Hello.

1073
01:09:28,748 --> 01:09:29,949
